 ## Acceptance Criteria
 
-| AC | Given / When / Then | Primary tasks |
-|---|---|---|
-| **AC1** | **Given** a projection annotated `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.ActionQueue, WhenState = "Pending,Submitted")]`. **When** `{TypeName}View` renders with non-empty data. **Then** the generated body emits a compact `FluentDataGrid` verified against three independent sub-ACs: **AC1a (Grid shape + ordering)** ÔÇö grid inline-includes the column defined by the projection's first `[ProjectionBadge]`-annotated property if present (ordering proxy), OR the first `DateTime`/`DateTimeOffset` property, OR declaration order as final fallback, with `DescendingByDefault = true` on that column; per-row `<CascadingValue Value="_rowContext" IsFixed="true">` wraps each row's action surface (D14). **AC1b (Inline action column)** ÔÇö when the projection declares inline commands (Story 2-2 renderer surface), the action column renders at the tail of the grid with button components pre-fill derivable fields from `_rowContext`. **AC1c (WhenState filter application)** ÔÇö `state.Items` is filtered client-side to rows whose state-enum property value matches any member of the parsed `WhenStates` list (`"Pending", "Submitted"` after trim); row count displayed equals the FILTERED count, not the full `Items.Count`; filter result is memoized by reference-equality on `state.Items` per D10 (C1). **AC1d (Row-context isolation ÔÇö F4 per review round 2)** ÔÇö when navigation away from an ActionQueue view triggers a route change that loads a DIFFERENT projection view on the same circuit, the new view's `_rowContext` MUST be fresh (its `AggregateId` equals the first item of the new projection, not the last-clicked item of the previous view). Verified via a bUnit test that renders two ActionQueue views on the same `TestContext`, clicks a row in view-A, navigates to view-B via a stubbed `NavigationManager`, asserts view-B's `ProjectionContext.AggregateId != view-A's last-clicked AggregateId`. Guards against `IsFixed="true"` cascade leaks on layout-owned hosts. **And** the subtitle (AC6) renders `"N {entityPlural} awaiting your action"`. Each sub-AC passes or fails independently ÔÇö the Dev Agent MUST report which clause failed in Completion Notes. | T1, T2, T3, T4 |
-| **AC2** | **Given** a projection annotated `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.StatusOverview)]`. **When** `{TypeName}View` renders. **Then** the generated body groups `state.Items` by the projection's status-enum property value and emits a `FluentDataGrid` whose rows are status ÔåÆ count aggregates (one row per distinct status, sorted by descending count). **And** each row carries a click handler dispatching `NavigationManager.NavigateTo(FcProjectionRoutes.StatusFilter(bcRoute, statusValue))` (H2 indirection per D11) ÔÇö the filtered-DataGrid destination for Story 4.3; the nav-fires assertion uses a bUnit `NavigationManagerInterceptor` and checks the URL STRING returned by the helper, not hard-coded format. **And** the subtitle renders `"N total across M statuses"`. **And** when the projection has no recognisable status-enum property (none of its enum properties carry `[ProjectionBadge]`), HFC1022 does NOT fire (the fallback is silent ÔÇö StatusOverview degrades to "N entities total"); this is by design because fixing "no status column" is an adopter-side modelling decision, not a generator warning. **ÔÜá Deferred-verify marker (per Bob review / G4):** the click-through DESTINATION (`?filter=status:X` query-string ÔåÆ filtered DataGrid) is Story 4.3's responsibility. For Story 4-1, AC2 is closed when (a) the navigation event FIRES with the correct URL, verified via a bUnit `NavigationManagerInterceptor` stub, AND (b) a `[DeferredVerify(Story = "4.3")]` marker is attached to the AC in Completion Notes. 4-1 DOES NOT depend on 4.3 landing ÔÇö AC2's navigation-fires test is the v1 gate. | T2, T3 |
-| **AC3** | **Given** a projection annotated `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.DetailRecord)]`. **When** `{TypeName}View` renders with a single entity in `state.Items` (or with `state.Items.Count > 1`, the first entity is rendered ÔÇö the multi-row selector lands in Story 4.5 expand-in-row). **Then** the generated body emits a `FluentCard` verified against two sub-ACs: **AC3a (Card structure)** ÔÇö vertical field list inside the card; primary fields (first 6 declaration order ÔÇö see D12) as top-level `<FluentLabel>` / `<FluentText>` pairs; when total supported properties Ôëñ 6 the accordion is OMITTED to avoid empty-accordion DOM noise. **AC3b (Secondary accordion)** ÔÇö when total supported properties > 6, properties in positions 7+ render inside a single `<FluentAccordion Expanded="false">` section. **And** the subtitle renders `"{EntityName} overview"` (AC6 ÔÇö copy nudge per Sally). **And** when `state.Items` is empty the Empty shell (AC8) runs ÔÇö NOT a blank card. Each sub-AC passes or fails independently. | T2, T3 |
-| **AC4** | **Given** a projection annotated `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.Timeline)]`. **When** `{TypeName}View` renders. **Then** the generated body emits a vertical list with one row per `state.Items` entry, ordered by the projection's first `DateTimeOffset` or `DateTime` property descending (most recent first), rendering as `<FluentStack Orientation="Vertical">` with each item carrying a `FluentPersona`-style timestamp + domain label + status-badge column (badge renders as humanized text until Story 4.2 lands colour). **And** the subtitle renders `"N events"`. **And** when the projection has no date/time property, the transform stage emits HFC1022 (Warning) `"Timeline projection {type} has no DateTime property ÔÇö ordering falls back to declaration order"` and the runtime renders declaration-order. | T2, T3 |
-| **AC5** | **Given** a projection with NO `[ProjectionRole]` annotation. **When** `{TypeName}View` renders. **Then** the generated body emits the Default strategy: a standard compact `FluentDataGrid<T>` with `PropertyColumn<T, string?>` entries (one per non-unsupported property), sortable headers (default `FluentDataGrid` sort ÔÇö no filter chips until Story 4.3), no inline-action column (inline actions surface in AC1's ActionQueue path only). **And** the subtitle renders `"N {entityPlural}"`. **And** this matches the existing Story 1-5 emitter output plus the new subtitle component ÔÇö the Default path is explicitly a **drop-in compatible extension**, not a rewrite, so existing `CounterProjectionView.approved.cs` snapshot diffs boil down to "subtitle + loading shell + empty shell inserts" (no column changes, no removals). **DoD gate (per Bob review):** the Story 1-5 default-path regression test suite (`CounterProjectionApprovalTests` + `RazorEmitterDefaultBodyShapeTests` + any other Story-1-5 anchor tests) MUST be green before AC5 is marked closed ÔÇö the Dev Agent explicitly logs the pre-change test run and the post-change test run in Completion Notes. If any Story 1-5 test regresses beyond the expected three inserts, AC5 stays OPEN and the regression is root-caused before re-baseline. | T2, T3, T5 |
-| **AC6** | **Given** any generated projection view. **When** the view title renders. **Then** `FcProjectionSubtitle` emits a subtitle `<p class="fc-projection-subtitle">` whose copy matches: ActionQueue = `HomeActionQueueSubtitleTemplate` (`"{0} {1} awaiting your action"` / `"{0} {1} en attente d'action"`); StatusOverview = `HomeStatusOverviewSubtitleTemplate` (`"{0} total across {1} statuses"` / `"{0} au total dans {1} statuts"`); Default = `HomeDefaultSubtitleTemplate` (`"{0} {1}"` with entity-plural); DetailRecord = `HomeDetailSubtitleTemplate` (`"{0} overview"` / `"{0} - aper├ºu"` ÔÇö per Sally's review: "detail" landed flat as a breadcrumb; "overview" reads as an intimate heading); Timeline = `HomeTimelineSubtitleTemplate` (`"{0} events"` / `"{0} ├®v├®nements"`). **And** when `IBadgeCountService` is registered, the count value comes from `Counts.GetValueOrDefault(projectionType, 0)`; when absent, the count falls back to `state.Items?.Count ?? 0`. **And** entity-plural uses `DisplayAttribute.GroupName`-or-`Name`-or-humanized `TypeName` resolution chain (existing `RazorModelTransform.ResolveHeader` pattern). **Loading-state rendering (SCAMPER-M round 3):** during `state.IsLoading == true`, `FcProjectionSubtitle` renders an EMPTY fragment (`<></>`) ÔÇö not `"0 entities"`. Rendering `"0 entities"` during load is a visual flash-of-false-info before data arrives; empty fragment keeps the subtitle slot reserved in layout (Blazor renders nothing visible) and fills only when data lands. Matches UX-DR44's "contextual subtitles orient business users" ÔÇö a wrong count doesn't orient; it misleads. | T6, T7 |
-| **AC7** | **Given** the `ProjectionRole` enum shipped by Contracts (`ActionQueue`, `StatusOverview`, `DetailRecord`, `Timeline`, `Dashboard`). **When** a new role value is proposed. **Then** the addition requires a cross-story spec change ÔÇö 4-1 freezes the attribute-side enum at 5 values + the `Default` synthetic transform sentinel (no sixth user-facing value in v1). **And** if Parse encounters an `int`-based role value outside the enum (e.g., adopter unsafe cast), Transform maps to `ProjectionRenderStrategy.Default` and `HFC1024_UnknownProjectionRoleValue` is emitted (Warning per D15, split from HFC1022 at round 2 ÔÇö H6) with `"Unknown ProjectionRole value {intValue} on {type} ÔÇö falling back to Default rendering."` **And** the transform-stage enum adds `Default` as a sentinel, NEVER surfaced through the `[ProjectionRole]` attribute (the attribute has no way to express "default" ÔÇö absence IS default). | T2, T7 |
-| **AC8** | **Given** any generated projection view, regardless of role. **When** `state.IsLoading == true`. **Then** the body renders `<FcProjectionLoadingSkeleton ColumnCount="N" RowCount="5" />` where N = count of non-unsupported properties (capped at 8 to stay close to the default DataGrid visual budget). **And** the skeleton container carries `aria-busy="true"` + `role="status"`. **When** `state.Items is null || state.Items.Count == 0` AND `state.IsLoading == false`. **Then** the body renders `<FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder ProjectionType="@typeof({TypeName})" />`. **When** `state.Items.Count > 0`. **Then** the strategy-specific body renders per AC1-AC5. **And** the three-way branch replaces the existing Story 1-5 "if loading / if empty / render grid" inline blocks ÔÇö the new shared `EmitLoadingShell` / `EmitEmptyShell` emitter helpers are the single source of truth. | T2, T3, T5 |
-| **AC9** | **Given** `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.ActionQueue, WhenState = "Pending,Submitted")]` on a projection whose status enum type declares members `Pending`, `Submitted`, `Approved`, `Rejected`. **When** Parse evaluates the attribute. **Then** `ProjectionRoleWhenState = "Pending,Submitted"` lands on `DomainModel` verbatim. **When** Transform processes the model. **Then** `WhenStates = ["Pending", "Submitted"]` lands on `RazorModel` (CSV-split, `Trim()`, ordinal-case `StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries`). **Given** the CSV contains an unknown member (`"Pending,Xxxx"`). **When** Parse evaluates the attribute. **Then** HFC1022 Warning fires with `"ProjectionRole.WhenState on {type} references unknown enum member 'Xxxx' ÔÇö member will be treated as always-no-match at runtime. Valid members: Pending, Submitted, Approved, Rejected."` (the diagnostic MUST list the known valid member names verbatim ÔÇö F6 per review round 2, to short-circuit the most common adopter failure mode: casing typos like `"pending"` vs `"Pending"`). **Member list cap (War Room round 3):** if the status-enum declares more than 10 members, the diagnostic lists the first 10 alphabetically plus `"ÔÇª and {N} more"` ÔÇö prevents a 200-member enum from producing a wall-of-text warning. AND the Transform stage still passes `Xxxx` through to `WhenStates` (renderer compares as string; unknown members simply never match, which is the correct fail-soft). **Given** an empty `WhenState = ""`. **When** Parse evaluates the attribute. **Then** `ProjectionRoleWhenState = null` (empty CSV = absent); runtime renders every row regardless of state. | T1, T2 |
-| **AC10** | **Given** `[ProjectionRole(ProjectionRole.Dashboard)]` on a projection. **When** Transform processes the model. **Then** `RazorModel.Strategy = ProjectionRenderStrategy.Dashboard` AND Emit dispatches to `EmitDashboardBody` which delegates to `EmitDefaultBody` (same DataGrid output as the no-attribute case). **And** HFC1023 Information fires `"Dashboard projection rendering is deferred to Story 6-3 ÔÇö {type} falls back to Default DataGrid rendering in v1."` **once per Dashboard-annotated projection per compilation ÔÇö see D16 for dedup ownership (round 4: no HashSet required; Roslyn's `IIncrementalGenerator` per-input invocation provides the "once per type" guarantee; incremental-cache hits bypass re-emission per D19 + T1.8)**. **And** the subtitle still renders the Default-strategy `"N {entityPlural}"` (Dashboard role has no canonical subtitle copy in v1). Dashboard is reserved ÔÇö not broken. | T2, T3, T7 |
-| **AC11** | **Given** `FcProjectionSubtitle` is registered in the Shell assembly. **When** it resolves `IBadgeCountService` via nullable DI (`IServiceProvider.GetService`). **Then** a present service wins for the count value ÔÇö the subtitle reads `service.Counts.GetValueOrDefault(projectionType, 0)` AND subscribes to `service.CountChanged` (filtered to the projection type) to refresh on updates. **And** when the service is absent (adopter has not registered `IBadgeCountService` ÔÇö not the default Shell, but allowed for v1.x adopters using their own badge source), the subtitle falls back to `state?.Items?.Count ?? 0` by reading `IState<{TypeName}State>` via the projection-type-specific generated hook (each generated view passes its `state.Items.Count` as a cascading value `SubtitleFallbackCount` ÔÇö avoids reflection-over-generic-state). **And** disposal unsubscribes from `CountChanged` ÔÇö no leaked subscriptions across circuit teardown (mirrors 3-5 D20 disposal discipline). **And** if `IBadgeCountService.CountChanged.Subscribe(...)` THROWS during `OnInitialized` (misconfigured service, Rx internal error), the subtitle catches the exception, logs it via `ILogger.LogWarning` (one-shot per component instance), and degrades to subtitle-without-count (identical to "service absent" branch) ÔÇö matches Story 3-5's "degrade gracefully on Badge service failure" ethos per FMA round 3. Similarly, `_countSubscription?.Dispose()` during `DisposeAsync` wraps in try/catch so a throwing observer doesn't break circuit teardown. | T3, T6 |
-| **AC12** | **Given** the shell's French locale. **When** any generated view renders with a French culture. **Then** the subtitle + empty-placeholder copy resolves from `FcShellResources.fr.resx`. **And** the existing `CanonicalKeysHaveFrenchCounterparts` test passes with the new 8 keys added to both files (58 ÔåÆ 66 per locale). **And** the three highest-emotional-weight keys (`HomeActionQueueSubtitleTemplate`, `HomeDefaultSubtitleTemplate`, `HomeEmptyPlaceholderText`) have a native-French-speaker pre-merge review attached to the PR per D19 (follows Story 3-5 D19 precedent ÔÇö not all 8 gated, just the three first-impression strings). | T8 |
