+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] Generated views never pass `IsLoading` into `FcProjectionSubtitle`, so the subtitle's loading-suppression path is dead and loading views can flash stale counts before data arrives [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/RazorEmitter.cs:222; src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/Components/Rendering/FcProjectionSubtitle.razor.cs:77]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] Generated loading shells never pass `EntityLabel` into `FcProjectionLoadingSkeleton`, so the aria-label falls back to the generic `items` label instead of the projection name promised by the shell component contract [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/RazorEmitter.cs:237; src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/Components/Rendering/FcProjectionLoadingSkeleton.razor.cs:51]
+- [ ] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `EmitActionQueueBody` still misses the AC1/D10 behavior it claims to ship: the filtered query is rebuilt on every render, no ActionQueue-specific ordering is applied, and the trailing action column is emitted as an always-empty placeholder [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:48]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `EmitStatusOverviewBody` relies on `FluentDataGrid<dynamic>` plus `Expression<Func<dynamic,...>>`, which is brittle and can fail once the generated view is compiled because dynamic member access is being embedded into expression trees [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:100]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `EmitStatusOverviewBody` assumes a non-null, `int`-backed enum when it sorts and routes rows (`(int)(object)g.Status!` / `(Enum)(object)row.Item.Status!`), so nullable statuses or custom underlying enum types can break the generated view [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:96]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `FcProjectionSubtitle` formats `HomeStatusOverviewSubtitleTemplate` with `(count, entityPlural)` instead of `(totalCount, distinctStatusCount)`, so StatusOverview subtitles do not match AC2/AC6 and the FR theory is currently blessing the wrong shape [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/Components/Rendering/FcProjectionSubtitle.razor.cs:155]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `EmitTimelineBody` calls `.ToString("g", ...)` directly on the chosen date property, which breaks nullable timestamp projections even though nullable DateTime columns are allowed elsewhere in the generator [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:205]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `EmitDetailRecordBody` documents Fluent UI label/value rendering but actually emits raw `div`/`strong` markup, so the DetailRecord body does not match AC3a or the component contract described in the story [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:334]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] The emitter comments promise Transform-stage `HFC1022` fallbacks for ActionQueue/Timeline projections missing a supporting status/date property, but `RazorModelTransform` only emits `HFC1023`/`HFC1024`, leaving the documented negative-path diagnostics unimplemented [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:62; src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Transforms/RazorModelTransform.cs:16]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `FcProjectionSubtitle` derives entity labels directly from the CLR type name and ignores the Display-friendly resolution chain called out in AC6 (`DisplayAttribute.GroupName` / `Name` / humanized fallback), so localized/friendly projection names never reach subtitle copy [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/Components/Rendering/FcProjectionSubtitle.razor.cs:128]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] `ResolveAggregateIdProperty` looks for `{TypeName}Id` without stripping the `Projection` suffix and `EmitRowContextActionColumn` emits `?.ToString()` against the resolved property, so common shapes like `OrderId` are missed and non-nullable struct ids can generate invalid code [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/RoleBodyHelpers.cs:75; src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools/Emitters/ProjectionRoleBodyEmitter.cs:279]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] The FR empty-placeholder aria label is still grammatically broken (`Aucun {0} trouv├®`) even though the visible empty text was the only string explicitly deferred to English identity-pass; the accessibility copy needs its own follow-through [src/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/Resources/FcShellResources.fr.resx:246]
+- [x] \[Review\]\[Patch\] The new guardrail tests are still partially brittle: they hard-code `D:/Hexalith.FrontComposer` paths, the approval diff gate collapses content into a `HashSet` instead of comparing line-level output, and the cache-hit coverage only asserts Parse-stage reuse instead of the full pipeline it claims to protect [tests/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools.Tests/Emitters/RazorEmitterStrategyDispatchTests.cs:266; tests/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools.Tests/Emitters/CounterProjectionApprovalTests.cs:94; tests/Hexalith.FrontComposer.SourceTools.Tests/Incremental/IncrementalGeneratorCacheHitTests.cs:36]
