+# Story 4.3: DataGrid Filtering, Sorting & Search
+
+Status: ready-for-dev
+
+> **Epic 4 ┬º 100ÔÇô142** ┬À **FR12** ┬À **UX-DR40** (DataGrid filtering surfaces) ┬À **UX-DR41** (filter persistence + empty-filtered state) ┬À **NFR87** (first-task completion < 30s with zero training) ┬À applies lessons **L01, L02, L03, L04, L06, L07, L09, L10, L11**. Consumes the `GridViewSnapshot` / `CaptureGridStateAction` / `RestoreGridStateAction` reducer contract frozen in Story 2-2 D30 and the persistence effects landed in Story 3-6 ADR-050; consumes Story 1-5's `ColumnModel.TypeCategory` routing; consumes Story 4-1's role-dispatched `Emit{Strategy}Body` shell and Story 4-2's `FcStatusBadge` + `SlotAppearanceTable` for status-chip rendering. Provides the FIRST shipped PRODUCER of `CaptureGridStateAction` ÔÇö turning the 2-2 / 3-6 "half-a-state-machine" into an end-to-end filter/sort/search loop across sessions.
+
+---
+
+## Executive summary (Feynman-level, ~45 sec)
+
+Today every generated projection view renders `state.Items.AsQueryable()` into a bare `FluentDataGrid` with no filter UI, no sort UI, no search box, and no persistence write-path. Story 2-2 shipped a reducer that captures `GridViewSnapshot` (scroll + filters + sort + expanded row) but nothing dispatches `CaptureGridStateAction`. Story 3-6 shipped the persistence effects (`DataGridNavigationEffects.HandleCaptureGridState` + `HandleRestoreGridState`) but no renderer calls them. Story 4-3 is where the loop closes: **the generated view dispatches on filter/sort/search change, the reducer updates `ViewStates`, the effect debounces and persists, and the next visit restores.**
+
+1. **Column filters ÔÇö `FluentSearch` in every column header.** `RazorEmitter` emits a `FluentSearch` into the `HeaderCellItemTemplate` of every `PropertyColumn` whose `TypeCategory Ôêê { Text, Numeric, Enum, DateTime }` (Boolean and Collection get no filter affordance ÔÇö D14 + HFC1027 Information for the Collection case). Typing into the search box fires a 300 ms debounce (`TimeProvider`-anchored cancellation-token pattern mirroring Story 3-6 D16) that dispatches `ColumnFilterChangedAction(viewKey, columnKey, filterValue)`. The reducer updates `GridViewSnapshot.Filters`; the effect persists.
+2. **Status filter chips.** When the projection has at least one enum column with `[ProjectionBadge]` mappings (reusing Story 1-4's `ColumnModel.BadgeMappings` IR field), the emitter renders a `<FcStatusFilterChips>` strip ABOVE the grid. The component loops over the DISTINCT `BadgeSlot` values present in `state.Items` and renders one `FluentBadge` toggle chip per slot, reusing Story 4-2's `SlotAppearanceTable` for color. Toggling a chip flips `Appearance.Tint` (inactive) Ôåö `Appearance.Filled` (active) and dispatches `StatusFilterToggledAction(viewKey, slotName)`. Multiple slots can be active simultaneously (OR semantics).
+3. **Global search ÔÇö adopter hook, not framework feature.** The generated view resolves `IProjectionSearchProvider<T>` via nullable DI (`IServiceProvider.GetService<...>()`). When the service is registered, a `<FcProjectionGlobalSearch>` renders below the view title; when absent, the component is OMITTED from the render tree ÔÇö no empty search box, no placeholder (per UX-DR40's "framework hook" design and Story 3-5 D15 nullable-DI precedent). Typing into the search box fires the same 300 ms debounce and dispatches `GlobalSearchChangedAction(viewKey, query)`. The adopter's provider implements `Task<IReadOnlyList<T>> SearchAsync(string query, CancellationToken)` ÔÇö 4-3 wires the hook; it does NOT ship a reference full-text implementation.
+4. **Server-side routing via `QueryRequest` extensions.** Column filters, status filters, search query, and sort order all travel through the existing `QueryRequest` record as additive nullable fields (`ColumnFilters`, `StatusFilters`, `SearchQuery`, `SortColumn`, `SortDescending`). The `Filter` legacy field (Story 1-3 stub) is `[Obsolete]` soft-deprecated per D18. ETag caching continues to work unchanged ÔÇö query parameters are part of the cache key composition already per NFR19.
+5. **Persistence via the 2-2 / 3-6 pipeline.** Every filter/sort/search change dispatches `CaptureGridStateAction(viewKey, snapshot)` where `viewKey` = `"{boundedContext}:{projectionTypeFqn}"` (Story 2-2 D30 format). Story 3-6 `DataGridNavigationEffects.HandleCaptureGridState` takes over with its 250 ms per-viewKey debounce; writes land in LocalStorage under `{tenantId}:{userId}:datagrid:{viewKey}`. On view mount, `{TypeName}View.OnInitialized` dispatches `RestoreGridStateAction(viewKey)`; 3-6's effect reads the blob and dispatches `GridViewHydratedAction` which the 2-2 reducer applies before the first data fetch.
+6. **Filter visibility + reset + empty-filtered state.** `FcFilterSummary` renders a row below the grid header when any filter is active: `"Filtered: Status = Pending, Approved | Name = \"foo\" | 12 of 47 orders"`. A `FcFilterResetButton` (Outline appearance) dispatches `FiltersResetAction(viewKey)` which the 2-2 reducer translates to clearing the snapshot's Filters/SearchQuery/StatusFilters AND 3-6's `HandleClearGridState` effect removes the persisted blob. `FcFilterEmptyState` activates when filters are active AND `state.Items.Count == 0` AND `state.TotalCount > 0` ÔÇö distinct from Story 4-1's `FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder` which handles the zero-total-items case (Story 4-6 takes that over later).
+7. **Keyboard affordance.** A new `/` shortcut registers via Story 3-4's `IShortcutService`; the handler is scope-gated (only fires when `document.activeElement` is inside a DataGrid ÔÇö matches Story 3-4 D12 focus-scope pattern) and focuses the first column filter input in the active grid.
+8. **Schema stability via reserved-key packing.** `GridViewPersistenceBlob` from Story 3-6 has a `Filters: Dictionary<string, string>` field ÔÇö instead of extending the blob schema (which would trip `GridViewPersistenceBlobSchemaLockedTests.BlobSerializesToExpectedJsonShape`), 4-3 packs status filters and global search into the same dictionary under reserved keys (`__status` = CSV of active slot names, `__search` = search query). No schema bump, no blob migration; the 3-6 contract stays frozen per D3.
+
+The design honors the "capability contract" principle: Fluxor state shape unchanged (reducer consumes additional actions, never new fields), persistence blob unchanged, diagnostic IDs reserved up-front (HFC1027), decisions live inside the L06 feature-story cap (Ôëñ 25 ÔÇö 4-3 targets 22), and every cross-story seam is explicit (L01). Scope is deliberately narrow: **filters/sort/search + persistence ÔÇö nothing else.** Virtual scrolling (4.4), expand-in-row (4.5), empty states with CTAs (4.6), `FcColumnPrioritizer` (4.4), and `FcNewItemIndicator` (FR21 / 3-5 follow-up) are OUT of scope.
+
+---
+
+## Dev Agent Cheat Sheet (L11)
+
+**Goal (one sentence):** Wire per-column `FluentSearch` filters + status-chip toggles + optional `IProjectionSearchProvider<T>` global search + sortable column headers through the generated view into the Story 2-2 / 3-6 persistence pipeline, with a 300 ms debounce, filter visibility summary, reset action, empty-filtered state, and `/` keyboard focus ÔÇö all server-side via `QueryRequest` extensions and all persisted per bounded-context:projection-type in LocalStorage.
