+
+## Story
+
+As a business user,
+I want to filter, sort, and search within DataGrid views ÔÇö with column filters, status toggle chips, and an optional global search ÔÇö and have my preferences remembered across sessions,
+so that I can quickly find the items I need without re-applying my filters every time.
+
+**Business value:** Until 4-3 lands, every generated DataGrid requires the business user to eyeball-scan 47 rows to find the three `Pending` orders they care about. After 4-3 ships, the user clicks a Pending status chip once and the grid collapses to 3 rows; next session the chip is already active. For a credit analyst triaging a queue or a fulfillment ops lead chasing exceptions, this is the difference between "I can use this" and "I need a custom view". NFR87 (first-task completion < 30s with zero training) is UNREACHABLE without 4-3. It is also the story that finally operationalizes Story 2-2's reducer-only state and Story 3-6's effect-only persistence ÔÇö 4-3 is the producer that turns the half-a-state-machine into a closed loop. Every generated view, across every role strategy from 4-1, gains filter/sort/search for free.
