+## Critical decisions (READ FIRST ÔÇö do NOT revisit)
+
+> **22 binding decisions.** Feature-story budget is Ôëñ 25 (L06). 4-3 lands at 22/25, leaving a 3-decision buffer for review rounds before Occam / Matrix trimming is required. Raise a spec-change proposal before revisiting any entry.
+
+| # | Decision | Rationale | Consumed by |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| **D1** | **Server-side is the only filter/sort/search routing.** `ColumnFilterChangedAction` ÔåÆ reducer ÔåÆ `CaptureGridStateAction` ÔåÆ 3-6 effect ÔåÆ next `LoadAction` carries a `QueryRequest` with the filter state ÔåÆ `IQueryService.QueryAsync` ÔåÆ server-filtered result. 4-3 does NOT filter `state.Items` client-side after a data fetch. | Server-side respects NFR19 (ETag-scoped per-tenant cache ÔÇö pre-filter caching would duplicate every cache entry per filter permutation), honors the PRD's auto-generation contract (adopters don't write client filter logic), and keeps the client memory footprint bounded (no O(N┬▓) client grids). Rejected: (a) client-side `Items.Where(...)` over the already-fetched set ÔÇö feels cheap but breaks ETag cache semantics, loses pagination correctness, and encourages adopters to ship unfiltered `GetAll()` queries; (b) hybrid (client-side for <500 items, server-side for larger) ÔÇö the 500 threshold is Story 4-4's concern and mixing strategies here splits the test surface; (c) configurable-per-projection ÔÇö feature-flagging creates two emit paths to maintain. | T2, T3; AC1, AC2, AC4 |
+| **D2** | **`QueryRequest` extends additively with 5 nullable/defaulted fields.** `ColumnFilters: IReadOnlyDictionary<string, string>?`, `StatusFilters: IReadOnlyList<string>?` (enum-MEMBER names, not slot names ÔÇö the server-side projection knows nothing about `BadgeSlot`), `SearchQuery: string?`, `SortColumn: string?`, `SortDescending: bool` (default false). Legacy `Filter: string?` gains `[Obsolete(error: false)]`. | Additive preserves all Story 1-3 / 1-5 callsite compilation. `StatusFilters` is enum-MEMBER names because the server filters projection columns by their domain type's enum values ÔÇö `BadgeSlot` is a presentation concern. The generator resolves slot-to-members at emit-time via `ColumnModel.BadgeMappings` (reverse lookup: active slot ÔåÆ enum members that map to it). `[Obsolete(error: false)]` keeps v0.x building; removal scheduled for v1.0-rc2. Rejected: (a) REPLACE `Filter` with `ColumnFilters` ÔÇö breaks adopter code; (b) a sibling `QueryRequestV2` record ÔÇö version proliferation for what is a pure extension; (c) put the fields in a nested `FilterSpec` sub-record ÔÇö two-level record nesting is awkward to mutate and violates the architecture's "flat records where possible" ┬º110 guidance. | T2, T3, T5; AC1, AC2, AC4 |
+| **D3** | **Reserved keys `__status` and `__search` pack status-chip + search-query state into the existing `GridViewSnapshot.Filters` dictionary.** No schema change to `GridViewPersistenceBlob`; no field addition to `GridViewSnapshot`; `GridViewPersistenceBlobSchemaLockedTests.BlobSerializesToExpectedJsonShape` stays green. The Fluxor reducer dispatches filter actions that read/write these reserved keys. | Avoids a contract bump on a shape locked by Story 2-2 D30 + Story 3-6 ADR-050 ÔÇö two frozen contracts stay stable for the price of two well-named magic strings. C# property naming rules (identifiers cannot START with `_` followed by another `_` as the second char is unusual; adopters would need `@__status` escaped identifiers to collide ÔÇö no real-world adopter has this) make the prefix a safe partition. Rejected: (a) add `StatusFilters: EquatableList<string>` field to `GridViewSnapshot` ÔÇö cascades into blob schema bump, `BlobSerializesToExpectedJsonShape` regen, persisted blob migration; triples the scope; (b) a second dictionary `SpecialFilters: Dictionary<string, string>` ÔÇö doubles serialization surface for no real benefit; (c) a single reserved string `"__metadata"` holding JSON-encoded sub-state ÔÇö opaque + hard to inspect in LocalStorage devtools. | T1, T2, T3, T4; AC2, AC5 |
+| **D4** | **300 ms column-filter debounce is anchored on the INJECTED `TimeProvider`** (per-component `CancellationTokenSource` + `await Task.Delay(DebounceInterval, _timeProvider, token)`). The component OWNS the CTS; on `Dispose`, it cancels pending work. | Matches Story 3-6 D16 per-viewKey debounce pattern verbatim (consistency across the persistence layer) ÔÇö a reader familiar with `DataGridNavigationEffects` sees exactly the same pattern in `FcColumnFilterCell`. `TimeProvider.System` in production, `FakeTimeProvider` in tests ÔÇö lets us assert debounce semantics without real clock waits. Rejected: (a) real-clock `Task.Delay(300)` ÔÇö untestable without flakiness; (b) `System.Threading.Timer` ÔÇö ambient ThreadPool dependency, disposal race conditions; (c) RxJS-style observable combinators via `System.Reactive` ÔÇö unnecessary dependency for a single debounce. | T1, T4; AC1 |
+| **D5** | **`FcStatusFilterChips` reuses Story 4-2's `SlotAppearanceTable` as its color source** but does NOT compose `FcStatusBadge` ÔÇö it renders `FluentBadge` directly because chip toggling requires `Appearance` control (Filled vs Tint) that `FcStatusBadge` deliberately hides. | `FcStatusBadge` is for immutable status DISPLAY ÔÇö its `Slot` parameter resolves to a fixed appearance to preserve the semantic-color contract. A chip is a TOGGLE ÔÇö the same slot renders differently when active vs inactive. Coupling `FcStatusBadge` to both would require exposing `Appearance` which breaks 4-2's D1 contract (component API hides `Appearance`). Reusing `SlotAppearanceTable` as the color SOURCE means a future slot addition flows into both surfaces automatically. Rejected: (a) nest `FcStatusBadge` inside an `onclick` wrapper with a `style` override for Filled ÔÇö breaks zero-override CSS discipline (architecture ┬º30); (b) duplicate the slot-to-color mapping in `FcStatusFilterChips` ÔÇö violates L01 cross-story contract; (c) expose `Appearance` on `FcStatusBadge` via an internal-only method ÔÇö pollutes a frozen contract. | T1, T5; AC2 |
+| **D6** | **`IProjectionSearchProvider<T>` is an OPEN GENERIC adopter contract registered per projection type** ÔÇö `AddTransient<IProjectionSearchProvider<Orders>, OrdersSearchImpl>()`. The generated view resolves it via nullable DI; absence ÔåÆ search UI omitted from render tree (per UX-DR40 "framework hook, not framework feature"). | Open-generic matches the `IState<T>` / `IStore<T>` Fluxor pattern the Shell already consumes. Typed-per-projection means adopter search implementations are compile-time bound to a specific projection's shape. Nullable DI matches Story 4-1's `IBadgeCountService` consumer pattern ÔÇö no hidden "search not configured" empty affordance. Rejected: (a) non-generic `IProjectionSearchProvider` with runtime type dispatch ÔÇö breaks AOT/trim, requires reflection at search-invocation time; (b) `Func<string, CancellationToken, Task<IReadOnlyList<T>>>` delegate registration ÔÇö loses the named-interface IDE surface; (c) framework-provided default implementation that does substring match on `state.Items` ÔÇö violates D1 (server-side only) and contradicts UX-DR40. | T1, T2, T4; AC4 |
+| **D7** | **Global search and column filters are ORTHOGONAL but NOT COMPOSED.** When the user has column filters active AND types in global search, the server query carries both (`QueryRequest.ColumnFilters != null && SearchQuery != null`); the adopter's `IQueryService` decides how to combine. 4-3 does NOT prescribe AND / OR semantics. | The framework cannot know adopter intent ÔÇö "find Pending orders matching 'acme'" could mean (a) Pending AND name-contains-acme, (b) Pending OR anything-matching-acme, (c) keyword-search across a Pending-filtered subset. Adopter knows; framework enumerates what the user selected and ships it. Rejected: (a) force AND semantics with a documented contract ÔÇö adopters who want OR rewrite the interface later; (b) force OR ÔÇö less common, weirder default; (c) disable column filters when global search is active ÔÇö surprising UX regression. | T2; AC4 |
+| **D8** | **Filter reducers CHAIN into `CaptureGridStateAction` ÔÇö they do NOT bypass it.** Every filter action handler reads the current snapshot from `IState<DataGridNavigationState>`, computes the next snapshot, and dispatches `CaptureGridStateAction(viewKey, nextSnapshot)`. Story 2-2's existing reducer for `CaptureGridStateAction` applies the snapshot to `ViewStates`; Story 3-6's effect picks it up for persistence. | Single write path = single persistence path. Adding parallel write paths (`FilterStateUpdatedAction` with its own reducer) would require parallel effect wiring, doubling the surface. Chaining keeps 3-6's `HandleCaptureGridState` as the exclusive persistence gate. Rejected: (a) standalone reducers that update `Filters` directly without touching `CaptureGridStateAction` ÔÇö requires a parallel effect for persistence, breaks 3-6's "capture captures all" invariant; (b) batch-update action collecting N filter changes ÔÇö overkill for a debounced single-dispatch flow. | T3, T4; AC1, AC2, AC4, AC5 |
+| **D9** | **`OnInitialized` dispatches `RestoreGridStateAction(viewKey)` BEFORE the first `LoadAction`.** The generator emits: `OnInitialized ÔåÆ dispatch RestoreGridState ÔåÆ await Task.Yield() ÔåÆ compute effective filters from snapshot ÔåÆ dispatch LoadAction(filters, sort, search)`. The "render tick" primitive is literally `await Task.Yield()` (yields once to the Blazor/Fluxor dispatcher queue ÔÇö pinned per Winston/Amelia roundtable 2026-04-23). A cleaner explicit `TaskCompletionSource` grid-state-ready gate is acknowledged as the principled primitive but requires new effect-surface plumbing; Epic 5 SignalR reconciliation (Story 5-4) will replace `Task.Yield()` with a gated handshake and that seam is reserved in D9's hand-off paragraph. | Avoids a double-round-trip (unfiltered fetch + hydrate snapshot + re-fetch with filters). The "await one render tick" pattern is standard Blazor (`await Task.Yield()`) and gives the Fluxor dispatcher room to apply the hydrated state. Rejected: (a) fetch-then-apply (load unfiltered, then apply hydrated filter client-side) ÔÇö violates D1; (b) block `OnInitialized` on the effect's `Task` ÔÇö requires exposing the effect's async completion, polluting the effect surface; (c) hydrate synchronously via `IState.Value.ViewStates` ÔÇö only works after the 3-6 app-init hydrate pass has run, which isn't guaranteed at view-mount time (hydration is async). The restore dispatch + render-tick wait IS the guaranteed-ordering primitive. | T2, T3; AC5 |
+| **D10** | **The `/` keyboard shortcut is SCOPE-GATED to DataGrid focus.** Registration: `IShortcutService.Register("/", "SlashFocusFilterShortcutDescription", HandleSlashAsync)`. Handler reads `DataGridFocusScope.IsFocusWithinDataGrid()` (JS interop); when false, returns `false` (shortcut is transparent ÔÇö native `/` behaviour continues); when true, resolves the enclosing `[data-fc-datagrid="{viewKey}"]` container and calls `fc-datagrid.focusFirstColumnFilter(viewKey)`. | Global `/` capture is hostile ÔÇö many users have browser find-in-page bound to `/` via extensions or the browser itself (Vimium, plain Firefox). Scope-gating makes the shortcut additive, not disruptive. The `data-fc-datagrid` attribute is the DOM-side scope marker; the JS interop walks ancestors from `document.activeElement`. Rejected: (a) always capture `/` ÔÇö stomps on native and user-configured bindings; (b) require explicit focus on the grid container ÔÇö adds keyboard friction; (c) scope by focus AND a modifier (`Shift+/` = `?`) ÔÇö conflicts with help/shortcut-list shortcuts elsewhere. | T1, T6; AC1 |
+| **D11** | **`FcFilterEmptyState` activates on `(filters.Any() && filtered == 0 && total > 0)`** and is a DISTINCT component from `FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder`. The generator emits a three-way conditional: `if (state.IsLoading)` ÔåÆ skeleton; `else if (state.Items.Count == 0)` ÔåÆ pick between `FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder` (total=0 or total unknown) and `FcFilterEmptyState` (filters active + total>0); `else` ÔåÆ grid + filter UI. | Semantic separation: "no data exists yet" (teach the user to create some) vs "your filters hid your data" (teach the user to widen filters). The two UX actions are different ÔÇö one is a CTA to create, the other is a reset button. Story 4.6 will evolve `FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder` with a domain-specific CTA; `FcFilterEmptyState` stays untouched because its copy is filter-specific. Rejected: (a) one `FcEmptyState` with a mode flag ÔÇö conflates two distinct UX surfaces; (b) skip `FcFilterEmptyState` and reuse `FcProjectionEmptyPlaceholder` with different copy ÔÇö breaks Story 4.6's clean replacement; (c) render the grid with 0 rows (blank DataGrid + summary) ÔÇö "blank grid" is a surprising mental state; explicit empty-state message is better. | T1, T2, T3; AC6 |
+| **D12** | **Sort affordance uses `FluentDataGrid`'s built-in `PropertyColumn.Sortable="true"` + default sort mechanics.** The generator emits `Sortable="true"` on every column; `FluentDataGrid` surfaces column-header click-to-sort; the grid's `SortByAscending` / `SortByDescending` events (or the equivalent API) dispatch `SortChangedAction(viewKey, columnKey, isDescending)`. | Fluent UI ships sort UI ÔÇö reinventing it violates zero-override architecture ┬º30. Default `FluentDataGrid` sort supports keyboard, ARIA, prefers-reduced-motion out of the box. Rejected: (a) custom sort indicator component ÔÇö duplicates built-in affordance; (b) sort via dropdown above the grid ÔÇö unusual UX; (c) sort ONLY via command palette ÔÇö hidden affordance, violates NFR87 discoverability. | T2; AC1 |
+| **D13** | **Filter summary count comes from `state.TotalCount` (pre-filter) + `state.Items.Count` (post-filter), BOTH supplied by the server in `QueryResult`.** Generated view maps `QueryResult.TotalCount` to `state.TotalCount` via the existing Story 1-5 `LoadedAction` reducer. | The server already emits `TotalCount` per Story 1-3 contract. Client-side computation is impossible under D1 (server-side filter). Rejected: (a) cache unfiltered total client-side on first load and compare ÔÇö stales quickly under real-time updates; (b) separate `CountAsync` query ÔÇö doubles server round-trips; (c) omit the "of total" ÔÇö business users need the comparative context ("3 of 47" teaches the filter is narrowing; "3 orders" alone is ambiguous). | T1, T2; AC3 |
+| **D14** | **Boolean and Collection columns receive NO filter affordance.** Boolean: 3-state toggle is an EpicE 6 customization path (documented in Dev Notes). Collection: HFC1027 Information fires at emit time; the column's `HeaderCellItemTemplate` is omitted. | Boolean filters in DataGrids are a known UX trap ÔÇö "Show Active" as a chip is different from "Filter by Active=true". Without the chip-or-input ambiguity resolved, best-practice is to omit. Collections (`IReadOnlyList<T>`, `Dictionary`, `HashSet`) have no scalar value to filter on ÔÇö a count-based filter would be surprising; adopters with collection-column filter needs route through Epic 6 slot overrides. Rejected: (a) generic "is empty / is not empty" boolean ÔÇö cheap but rarely what users want; (b) auto-sum or auto-count filter ÔÇö surprising defaults; (c) render a disabled filter input with placeholder "not supported" ÔÇö visual clutter. | T2, T3, T7; AC1 |
