+
+## Story
+
+As a business user,
+I want DataGrids to handle large datasets smoothly via virtual scrolling and auto-manage column visibility when projections have many fields,
+so that performance stays fast on 500+-row projections and the view remains usable when a projection declares dozens of properties.
+
+**Business value:** Until 4-4 lands, every `OrdersProjection` with 5,000 rows is a render-tree materialization bomb ÔÇö opening the view stalls the browser tab for 3-4 seconds while Blazor builds the full DOM, and scrolling through is stuttery because every row is a real DOM node. After 4-4 ships, the same projection renders in < 200ms because only the ~15 visible rows are in the DOM at any time; scrolling triggers the Fluent `Virtualize` machinery which tears down off-screen rows and fetches server-side pages transparently. For a fulfillment operator scanning 5,000 daily orders or a finance analyst filtering a 10,000-row transaction ledger, this is the difference between "the tool loads" and "the tool is unusable." NFR4's "P95 render time < 300ms on 500 virtualized rows" is UNREACHABLE without 4-4. It is also the story that operationalises Story 2-2's reserved `ScrollTop` field (dormant since 2-2 landed) and unlocks the FR12 "smart browsing" promise for the common case of wide projections (>15 fields) where the current output is visually unwieldy.
