+| **D13** | **`ItemKey` is resolved at emit time via `ResolveItemKeyAccessor(model)` ÔÇö first-match over `Id` / `AggregateId` / `Key` property names.** Fallback: `x => x` (item-as-key ÔÇö Blazor will use reference equality, acceptable for immutable records). | `ItemKey` drives Blazor's `@key` directive inside the virtualized row renderer; stable keys prevent ghost-render bugs when pages swap in/out. Projection types generally expose an identifier field; first-match resolution covers DDD-style `AggregateId`, CRUD-style `Id`, and key-value shapes. Fallback to `x => x` is safe for records (value equality). Rejected: (a) require an `[ItemKey]` attribute on projection types ÔÇö friction for adopters; (b) use `HashCode.Combine` over all properties ÔÇö overhead per render; (c) fallback to `typeof(T).Name + index` ÔÇö breaks with reordering. | T1, T2; AC1 |
