+| **D16** | **`LoadedPageState.PendingCompletionsByKey` uses `TaskCompletionSource<object>` (non-generic) because Fluxor feature states are non-generic.** The `GridItemsProvider<T>` callback casts the resolved `object` to `IReadOnlyList<T>` ÔÇö type safety is lost at the dictionary boundary and recovered at the callback. Documented as a v1 seam. | Fluxor requires feature state to be concrete types (not open generics). `TaskCompletionSource<object>` sidesteps the generic constraint without introducing per-T feature states (which would multiply the state surface by the number of projections). The cast is safe-by-construction ÔÇö the effect always resolves with `IReadOnlyList<T>` where T matches the dispatch. Rejected: (a) `TaskCompletionSource<IReadOnlyList<object>>` ÔÇö forces an intermediate list copy; (b) per-projection feature state (`LoadedPageState<T>`) ÔÇö O(projection-count) feature types, registration bloat; (c) direct callback via `Func<int, int, Task<GridItemsProviderResult<T>>>` stored in state ÔÇö closures-in-state is a Fluxor anti-pattern (state must be serialisable); (d) generator emits a per-projection feature state ÔÇö same as (b). | T3, T6; AC2 |
