+## Dev Notes
+
+### Relevant architecture patterns and constraints
+
+- **Zero-override architecture** (`architecture.md:30`): `FluentDataGrid`, `FluentPopover`, `FluentCheckbox`, `FluentButton`, `FluentMessageBar` all consumed verbatim. No custom CSS, no token overrides. The `Virtualize` + `DisplayMode="Table"` pairing follows the Fluent team's own published guidance (`FluentDataGrid` MCP notes) ÔÇö we inherit their tuning, we don't second-guess.
+- **Convention-based rendering** (`architecture.md:493-497`): "IR metadata (field types, role hints, badge mappings)" ÔÇö 4-4 operationalises the (previously empty) `ColumnModel.Priority` IR field. After 4-4, every generated view has a cap on its visible-column count that scales with projection complexity.
+- **Fluxor single-source-of-truth discipline** (Story 1-3 ADR-008): every state change is an immutable `record` action; reducers are pure; effects are the only IO boundary. 4-4's `LoadPageAction` dispatches through `LoadPageEffects` (sole IO gate); the `ColumnVisibilityChangedAction` + `ScrollCapturedAction` reducers chain to Story 2-2's `CaptureGridStateAction` so persistence stays single-pipelined through Story 3-6's existing effect.
+- **IR cache stability** (Story 1-4 incremental-build contract): 4-4 adds `PropertyModel.ColumnPriority` + `ColumnModel.Priority` as derived fields; `RazorModel` unchanged in shape but carries the sorted `Columns` list. IR byte-stability preserved ÔÇö Story 1-4 cacheability tests stay green (the stable sort is deterministic over the same input).
+- **Blazor Server + Blazor Auto compatibility** (UX-DR59): `IJSRuntime` for scroll interop works in both modes; `DataGridScrollInterop` is circuit-scoped in Server, app-scoped in WASM (standard Blazor scope rules). The JS module `fc-datagrid.js` ships via the Shell's static web assets (`_content/Hexalith.FrontComposer.Shell/js/`).
+- **Persistence fail-closed** (L03 tenant isolation): relies on Story 3-6's existing fail-closed `TryResolveScope` in `DataGridNavigationEffects`. 4-4 does NOT add new scope-check code; it relies on the existing guard. `LoadPageEffects.HandleLoadPage` routes through `IQueryService.QueryAsync` which honours `QueryRequest.TenantId` (populated upstream). Any null/empty tenant short-circuits at the service boundary ÔÇö the 4-4 effect does not need its own guard because it's not persisting anything that could leak across tenants.
+- **NFR4 performance budget**: 500 virtualized rows P95 < 300ms. Fluent UI v5's `Virtualize` implementation renders only visible rows + `OverscanCount="3"` ÔÇö ~15-18 rows in the render tree at any time. Benchmark harness in T4.9 asserts this directly.
